This paper deals with improving the accuracy of CNN-based camera pose estimation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The modifications proposed in the paper involve data augmentation and the use of LSTM cells, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
